@Node "intro" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

SimpleView is started from @{"Ambient" link "wb"} or @{"Shell" link "use"} with one option; file. It shows a picture on an own 24bit screen.
Pictures are always entirely shown on the chosen screen, if the pictures is bigger than the biggest screen,
then the picture is downscaled to fit in that screen. 
Click with the mousepointer on the left upper corner of the picture to quits. You can press the "Q" and "Esc"
keys too for quiting.

SimpleView_WB is started from @{"Shell" link "use"} with one option; file. It shows picture in a window on the
default public screen, what's usual Ambient. Advantage of SimpleView_WB is the small filesize and
fast native MorphOS PowerPC machine code written programm. It make use of the datatypes system.
Filenames with spaces are read OK.

@EndNode
@Node "Distribution" 
@{b}Distribution and copyright@{ub}

SimpleView is freeware.

@EndNode
@Node "Tip" 
@{b}Tip@{ub}

I've installed SimpleView as viewer in the directory tool (Double)DrawerBall and old 68K Directory Opus Magellan 582.
My screenmode list for all color depth's:

1600 × 1200 50Hz
1280 × 1024 60Hz
1152 × 900 65Hz
1120 × 832 70Hz
1024 × 768 75Hz Ambient, standard
800 × 600 80Hz
768 × 576 85Hz For DVD playback
640 × 512 90Hz Amiga hi-res PAL interlace and for Bochs
640 × 480 92,5Hz
640 × 400 100Hz Amiga hi-res NTSC interlace and Atari ST hi-res
640 × 256 105Hz Amiga hi-res PAL
640 × 200 110Hz Amiga hi-res NTSC and Atari ST medium-res
320 × 256 130Hz (was 115Hz) Amiga low-res PAL
320 × 240 135Hz (was 120Hz)
320 × 200 140Hz (was 125Hz) Amiga low-res NTSC, Atari ST low-res and C64 (no borders)

There are maximal 15 screenmode's possible for each depth. Thus 15 screenmodes in 24bit,
15 screenmodes in 16bit and 15 screenmodes in 8bit. Screenmode with a high resolution as
1600 × 1200 are with lower frequencies. I'am tweaking which of the
two 1152 × 900 65Hz and 1120 × 832 70Hz are removed, these are nearly the same.
The frequencies are for old-fashioned monitors, not modern (TFT) flatscreens.


