@Node "use" "How to use SimpleView"

SimpleView is started from Shell.

@{u}@{b}Shell usage:@{uu}@{ub}

The following commandline options are supported:
------------------------------------------------

TEMPLATE:

	SimpleView,NAME

NAME=filename, picture. Filenames which contains spaces are read well.


Shell (CLI) Examples:
---------------------

@{fg shine}-1-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}SimpleView_WB DH0:Pegasos WingHorse.jpg@{fg text}

Shows the picture 'Pegasos WingHorse.jpg' in a window on the default publc screen, what's
mostly Ambient.

@{fg shine}-2-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}SimpleView_WB "Work:MorphOS Butterfly.png"@{fg text}

Shows the picture 'MorphOS Butterfly.png' in a window on the default publc screen, what's
mostly Ambient. Note: the charracter " can be used or not, makes no difference.

For SimpelView that put pictures on an own 24bit screen, same as above.
Click with the mousepointer on the left upper corner of the picture to quits.


@EndNode
@Node "wb" "Ambient"
@{b}Starting from Ambient@{ub}

SimpleView can be started from Ambient from the icon. A filerequester appears, choose more pictures:
press the "shift" button and click with the mouse on the desired pictures to view, or click with the left
mousebutton and move over the files, which becomes highlighted.
To see next picture, click with the mousepointer on the left upper corner of the picture or press the
"Q" or "Esc" keys. Don't  matters if you choose a file which is not a picture, SimpleView skips these
and loads next picture(s).
 

@EndNode
@Node "Require" "Requirements"

Minimal Requirements:

SimpleView_WB: MorphOS

SimpleView: MorphOS, 24bit screens

@EndNode
@Node "bugs" "Known bugs"

SimpleView_WB

- Pictures larger then the window are cutt.

- Other programms can't take acces to the picture as long SimpleView_WB holds.

SimpleView

- ARGB32 pictures can not be scaled down, it's mostly small icons

- when SimpleView do not quits by pressing "Escape" or "Q" key, klick with the left mousebutton at the picture.

- found that many PNG pictures are RGB24, means that SimpleView can scales them down !

@EndNode
@Node "tech" "Technical"

SimpleView_WB, SimpleView,  quits if a file can not be found or is no picture.
SimpleView quits if no 24bit screens are found

@EndNode
@Node "Compilation" "Compilation of SimpleView"
    
SimpleView is assembled with vasm & vlink from the vbcc C package.

Freeware software used:

MCalc -programmers suitable calculator.
Snoopium -shows much system calls, good for anylizing programs. (MOS)
Scout -shows much information about the Pegasos, also screens/windows (MOS)
AutoDocReader -to read autodocs that bescribes the Amiga/MorphOS functions. (MOS)
PPC680x0 -translate 68K sources to PPC, without it, this program was not possible.
CygnusEd Professional V4.23 PPC -famous texteditor. (MOS)

My Amiga configuration:

 Amiga1200T 68060 59Mhz, 603e 200Mhz, ROM 3.1, OS3.9 BB2, RAM 128Mb, SCSI HD 8Gb,
 IDE DVD 16x40x, SCSI CD-R 6x4x, PARALLELZIP 100Mb, FlickerFixer/Scandoubler,
 Mediator Voodoo5 graphics with picasso96

 Processor board is BlizzardPPC with SCSI2 (Overclocked the 68060 to 59Mhz)

 Pegasos II G4 1Ghz, MorphOS 1.4.5, 2.7, 1GbRAM, PHILIPS DVDR16LS Dual DVD with LIGHTSCRIBE,
 WD 120G HD, Belinea 107065 monitor, PixelView Pro TV-Radio, UMAX speakers,
 Radeon 9250, Elbox USB2 card (it's almost empty, they show an older model on their website www.elbox.com).
 Efika, MacMini 1.5Ghz

@EndNode
